## 📌 Project Overview

Infrastructure security starts with **Identity and Access Management (IAM)**. Before provisioning compute, storage, or networking resources in AWS, 
organizations establish access controls to ensure users and services have only the permissions they need.

In today's Terraform lab, I created an **AWS IAM policy** using Terraform that grants **read-only access to Amazon EC2 resources**, 
following the **Principle of Least Privilege (PoLP)**.

This project demonstrates how Infrastructure as Code (IaC) can be used to automate cloud security configurations in a consistent, repeatable, 
and version-controlled manner.

