# 🔑 IAM Policy Explained

The policy grants permission for:

```text
ec2:Describe*
```

This allows users to:

- Describe EC2 Instances
- Describe Volumes
- Describe Snapshots
- Describe Images (AMIs)
- Describe Availability Zones
- Describe VPCs
- Describe Security Groups
- Describe Network Interfaces

The policy **does not allow**:

- Launch EC2 instances
- Stop instances
- Start instances
- Reboot instances
- Terminate instances
- Create snapshots
- Delete snapshots
- Modify security groups

This makes it an ideal **read-only policy**.

